Dear colleagues,

Transmitting Science is offering the course "Species occurrence data 
download and cleaning with R" (8th edition).

Course webpage: 
https://www.transmittingscience.com/courses/ecology/species-occurrence-data-download-and-cleaning-with-r

Species occurrence data are essential for a range of ecological and 
biogeographical analyses. Although they are now widely available in 
multiple online sources, they are heterogeneous and come with caveats 
that need to be addressed before moving on with the analysis.

In this short course, we will use a range of tools to:
*    Import species occurrence data from various sources into R (e.g. 
GBIF, iNaturalist, VertNet, EcoEngine)
*    Join and arrange these data into a homogeneous dataset for analysis
*    Map and visually inspect the data for taxonomic and spatial errors 
and bias
*    Clean the data by removing detectable errors
*    Correct or minimise spatial bias

The course will be highly interactive and will include both theoretical 
and practical sessions. Participants are encouraged to work with their 
own species of interest, although several illustrative examples will 
also be provided.

For any questions, please write to courses at transmittingscience.com
Best regards,

Haris

